2 (3) Any violation under this section may be prosecuted in any county where:
3 (a) The defendant resides;
4 (b) The false report was communicated; or
5 (c) There was an emergency response to the false report.
6 (4) (a) The court, in imposing a sentence on a defendant who has been convicted of
7 any offense under this section, shall order restitution to:
8 1. Any agency or organization for the reasonable costs of the emergency
9 response incurred by that agency or organization resulting from the false
10 report; and
11 2. Any person who suffered damages caused by the agency or organization
12 that provided an emergency response.
13 (b) An order of restitution under this subsection shall, for the purpose of
14 enforcement, be treated as a civil judgment.
